1
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,750
[CROWD chattering]

2
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:42,916
Get your fresh-made
noodles over here!

3
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,750
Noodles over here!

4
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,666
[BIMII] Eruna, I can't
carry any more, ryui.

5
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:11,958
Jeez, how many fried octopus
balls can one girl eat anyway?

6
00:01:12,041 --> 00:01:14,000
You need to have more
faith in yourself, Bimii.

7
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:15,583
The only reason you
can't carry any more

8
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:17,125
is because you think you can't.

9
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:20,375
Look, if you give up, that's
the end of the octo balls.

10
00:01:20,458 --> 00:01:22,791
Don't let go of the takoyaki.
Don't let go!

11
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:24,916
[BIMII] And yet, your mania
for takoyaki is mild

12
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,083
compared to the rest
of your obsessions.

13
00:01:27,166 --> 00:01:30,250
Do you have enough points left
to spend on anything else now?

14
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:31,958
[BIMII] You've wasted
a lot on these suckers.

15
00:01:32,041 --> 00:01:34,750
Wasn't your plan today
to try and be more frugal?

16
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:37,958
[ERUNA]
I forgot.

17
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:40,083
[BIMII] Yeah, that's
what I thought, ryui.

18
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,333
[ERUNA]
Seisa! Hi!

19
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:48,416
Did you watch my first
match in the rookie battle?

20
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,083
Because I like totally won
and looked way cool.

21
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:53,333
[SEISA]
Well, of course I did.

22
00:01:53,416 --> 00:01:56,500
Eruna, I'm actually here
to give you a good luck hug

23
00:01:56,583 --> 00:01:57,666
if you want one.

24
00:01:57,750 --> 00:01:58,708
[gasps]

25
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:03,666
Well, that is, unless you
need more than just a hug.

26
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:06,583
Yes. More than a hug, please!

27
00:02:09,208 --> 00:02:10,708
[SEISA]
Poor thing.

28
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:12,958
She must've hit her head pretty
hard during the rookie battle.

29
00:02:13,041 --> 00:02:16,833
[BIMII] No. Believe it or not,
abnormal is her normal.

30
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:55,291
[ERUNA]
Hurry up, Seisa!

31
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:56,958
Come on, come on!

32
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:59,000
[laughing]

33
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,833
Look at all these
awesome food choices!

34
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:03,583
I want yakisoba and
okonomiyaki and takoyaki

35
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,958
and more takoyaki
and even more takoyaki.

36
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:07,750
[BIMII] So what I'm getting
here is that you might

37
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,166
be a fan of takoyaki.

38
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,541
Hey, Seisa, are you
craving anything specific?

39
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,375
[SEISA] I'm kind of in the
mood for something sweet.

40
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:14,458
Heck yeah!

41
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:15,791
Naturally, a sweet sauce
with takoyaki

42
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:17,166
is the best sauce with takoyaki,

43
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,583
which is why I got
a whole bunch!

44
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:20,958
It's so cool how you
always totally get me!

45
00:04:21,041 --> 00:04:22,500
Oh, and you don't need
to worry about the points.

46
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:24,250
I'll just get what
I need from Bimii.

47
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,541
[BIMII] I'm starting
to get a little worried

48
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,208
about your
confidence in me, ryui.

49
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:30,416
[MINATOGAWA]
Step right up.

50
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,625
Would anyone by
chance like to play?

51
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,916
[ERUNA]
Is that Minatogawa?

52
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,791
Why is he running a booth alone?

53
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:39,125
[BIMII] Because he is
the one and only member

54
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:41,333
of the flower
arrangement club, ryui.

55
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:42,583
[ERUNA]
That's right.

56
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:45,083
The other members
never showed up, did they?

57
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:48,958
You know, even for him,
he seems really out of it.

58
00:04:49,041 --> 00:04:51,333
Step right up to win...

59
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,000
It also looks like
he's trying to do that thing

60
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,583
where you smile so
you're more approachable,

61
00:04:54,666 --> 00:04:55,875
but what's happening
on his face right now

62
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:57,625
is not what he's going for.

63
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:03,333
Hey! What's up, Minatogawa?
Keeping busy?

64
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:05,208
Hey. Doing what I can.

65
00:05:05,291 --> 00:05:07,166
I never would've guessed
the flower arranging club

66
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,500
would have a shooting gallery.

67
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:10,250
Great idea!

68
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:11,375
Whoa, that's huge!

69
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:13,125
Guess what?
There's a big grand prize.

70
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:17,125
A genuine life-sized Super
Miracle Man action figure.

71
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,083
[ERUNA] Well it's way too big
to be knocked over

72
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:20,500
with one of those guns!

73
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:23,583
How old is that thing, anyway?
It looks like crap.

74
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:26,541
[MINATOGAWA] Guess what? He's an
old toy from my parents' house.

75
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,125
[ERUNA] It's used,
is that what you're saying?

76
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:29,875
Because if used is supposed
to make me want him,

77
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:31,250
it doesn't, like at all.

78
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:32,500
Oh, guess what?

79
00:05:32,583 --> 00:05:34,041
He's got a little tear
in his boot right here.

80
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,208
[ERUNA]
You can't use that!

81
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:36,708
No one wants a torn prize!

82
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,083
Well, guess what?

83
00:05:38,166 --> 00:05:39,750
He's my most prized possession.

84
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,750
[ERUNA] You're not
planning to give it away?

85
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:43,000
And guess what else?

86
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:45,166
[ERUNA] What else
could there possibly be?!

87
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:46,541
I gotta pee...

88
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,166
[ERUNA] Well then
go use the restroom.

89
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:51,166
And don't worry about the booth.
We'll keep an eye on it for ya!

90
00:05:52,958 --> 00:05:54,000
I know I shouldn't say this,

91
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,958
but that kid
is strange, ryui.

92
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:58,375
[ERUNA]
What a bummer.

93
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,166
No one's coming to check
out this booth at all.

94
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:02,958
It might as well be freakin'
invisible, am I right?

95
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,041
I hope he didn't plan on
that thing bringing in money,

96
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:06,958
because Miracle Man
is looking rough.

97
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:09,583
And check out how janky
these other toys are, too.

98
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:12,500
I mean, uh, check out
how well-loved they are.

99
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,791
These are Minatogawa's
personal toys

100
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,541
from when he was a little boy.

101
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,833
[ERUNA]
"Sadamashi Minatogawa."

102
00:06:19,916 --> 00:06:21,166
You're right!

103
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:22,875
And he spelled his name wrong,
which is adorable!

104
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:25,250
So he decided to use
his own toys from childhood

105
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,458
to be a part of his booth?

106
00:06:26,541 --> 00:06:28,166
Maybe you gotta have
a flower arranging brain

107
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:29,375
to get what that's about.

108
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:30,958
He's normally by himself,

109
00:06:31,041 --> 00:06:32,500
so having a booth might
have been what he thought

110
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:35,250
was a good way to have fun
with everyone else for a change.

111
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:36,833
[ERUNA]
I get it.

112
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:39,125
Well then, I'm going
to do whatever I can

113
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,958
to make this place rock!

114
00:06:43,916 --> 00:06:46,458
Come on, step right up
and take your best shot, kids!

115
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:49,125
Flower arrangers'
shooting gallery!

116
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:52,416
We even have our own
perfectly-arranged mascot!

117
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:54,416
And remember, the beauty
who shot through my heart

118
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,625
with one look
is absolutely free!

119
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,875
[BIMII] Might want to
okay that with her first.

120
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:02,083
[YUTO] I had a feeling the voice
piercing my brain had to be you.

121
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:03,791
Of course you'd
bring Seisa along.

122
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:05,166
So what's the deal here?

123
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:06,875
Why're you guys pimping out
another club's booth?

124
00:07:06,958 --> 00:07:08,458
That's so funny
because I had a feeling

125
00:07:08,541 --> 00:07:11,041
the dark soul I could
sense nearby was you!

126
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,250
Wanna try out
the shooting gallery?

127
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,250
Special deal just for Yuto!

128
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:16,708
What? That's not a deal!

129
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,583
I literally stood here and
watched you mark it up

130
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:20,083
to a higher price!

131
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:22,750
Actors always have
such vivid imaginations.

132
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,416
[YUTO] Besides,
why would I pay anything?

133
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:27,125
Look at those crummy prizes!
Who'd want to win that?

134
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:30,125
No... way...!

135
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:33,416
[BIMII]
What's wrong, ryui?

136
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,666
You couldn't possibly want
that Miracle Man, could you?

137
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,666
No, I don't want
any of this crap!

138
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,083
I'm only wondering if something
as big as that Miracle Man

139
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:43,250
could actually be knocked over,
so you know, guess I can try.

140
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:45,041
Might as well see
if I can do it.

141
00:07:48,583 --> 00:07:50,000
Oh, nice!

142
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:52,708
It may not be your scythe,
but you still look pretty cool!

143
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:55,875
[BIMII] I think those kids
might be here as customers.

144
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:57,375
If they all
want to play, ryui,

145
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:59,250
oh boy, we're gonna
rake in the points!

146
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,541
You can do it, Yuto!
Knock him over!

147
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:02,916
[YUTO]
Who you talking to, Eruna?

148
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,083
This kind of thing is my jam!

149
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:08,541
[panting]

150
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:11,791
[YUTO]
Get it together. Focus.

151
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:14,541
Miracle Man,
you're gonna be mine!

152
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:19,000
[gasps]

153
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:20,666
[ERUNA]
It didn't even budge!

154
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,041
Uh oh, ryui.

155
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:23,625
All our new customers
are starting to talk smack.

156
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,791
That thing didn't move
after being directly hit.

157
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:27,291
This looks totally rigged,
don't you think?

158
00:08:27,375 --> 00:08:28,583
Dude, try it again!

159
00:08:28,666 --> 00:08:29,375
'Kay!

160
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:30,916
[gunshot]

161
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,750
[gunshots]

162
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:39,208
Before I die,

163
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:42,500
I want you to please
grant me one final wish.

164
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:46,666
Eruna. Take care of
Miracle Man for me from now on.

165
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,333
No, don't leave me!

166
00:08:49,041 --> 00:08:52,500
I swear it. I shall avenge
your most tragic death.

167
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:53,791
Are you serious?

168
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:56,000
Yuto just died from
shooting a fake gun, ryui?

169
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:02,125
Oh great, so you're
going for overkill, then.

170
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,291
[ERUNA]
Yep! Go!

171
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,833
Ohmigah, they're right;
this game is totally rigged!

172
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:13,083
Call me crazy,

173
00:09:13,166 --> 00:09:14,166
but it looks like you
don't want to give up

174
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,916
that Miracle Man
of yours, Minatogawa,

175
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,458
even if someone could win it.

176
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:18,666
Very perceptive.

177
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,833
I guess it's hard
not to notice, though.

178
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,958
Hey, what did you just do?

179
00:09:24,041 --> 00:09:25,875
You're using Selfish Flower.

180
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,416
That I am.

181
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,916
Not surprised I can't fool the
great Seisa Mikagura's eyes.

182
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,291
Eruna, step away.

183
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:34,541
Don't let anyone close.

184
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:36,583
You'll fight? Really?

185
00:09:36,666 --> 00:09:38,750
If you say you'll let
Miracle Man go quietly,

186
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:39,916
then I won't have to.

187
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,500
So it's all up to you.

188
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:44,458
Well, unfortunately, I'm not
giving Miracle Man up.

189
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:47,916
Besides, I'd love
to fight you anyway.

190
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,541
It would honestly be
a dream come true for me.

191
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:53,333
Wait a minute, ryui!

192
00:09:53,416 --> 00:09:54,791
Seisa, don't tell me you're
going to use Killing Art

193
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:56,125
right here and now!

194
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:57,166
[gunshot]

195
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,666
[CROWD murmuring]

196
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:01,041
Did I just see
what I thought I saw?

197
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:02,875
Because it looks like
she went after an easier toy

198
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:04,458
and left Miracle Man alone.

199
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:05,916
She completely
avoided fighting him,

200
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,208
which isn't like
Seisa at all, ryui.

201
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:11,083
True enough, but check
out the face on Minatogawa now.

202
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,250
Sniff.

203
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:15,708
[ERUNA] Oh no! Poor fella.
He looks so sad.

204
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:17,041
[SEISA]
Come to me.

205
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:19,125
Minatogawa may have
loved Miracle Man more,

206
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:21,041
but this guy was a close second.

207
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:22,625
Uh, how would you know that?

208
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,458
I'm sure it has something
to do with their childhood,

209
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,375
and we'll always be
wondering about it, moving on.

210
00:10:26,458 --> 00:10:27,583
Hey, can I go next?

211
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,083
I wanna see if I can
take down Miracle Man!

212
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:30,166
I wanna play, too!

213
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,875
Uh, guess what?
Step right up!

214
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:35,375
One at a time, please.

215
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:42,875
[gunshots]

216
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:47,875
Aw, man,

217
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:50,375
you guys don't know where
Seisa ran off to, do ya?

218
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,333
[BIMII] No, she just
disappeared, ryui.

219
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:53,750
--Boo!
--On the bright side,

220
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:55,750
everyone looked like they
were having a good time.

221
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:58,083
Yeah, we did a good thing!

222
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:00,333
Minatogawa needed it.

223
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:01,833
He spends so much
time by himself

224
00:11:01,916 --> 00:11:04,041
in the flower arrangement club.

225
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,958
I bet he'd be really grateful
if someone would come by

226
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:08,541
and just hang out
with him, you know?

227
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:09,958
I have a thought.

228
00:11:10,875 --> 00:11:12,125
Why don't you be that someone

229
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:13,875
and go spend time with him
every once in a while?

230
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,916
It could be one of your
new club's activities!

231
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,875
Yeah, I think
I can handle that!

232
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:20,375
Except for...

233
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:22,666
I sorta haven't actually decided
what my new club should be

234
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:25,083
or should do or anything
about it at all, really.

235
00:11:25,166 --> 00:11:26,583
[BIMII] You've gotta
start remembering things!

236
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:27,625
[USAMARU]
Hey!

237
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,250
We've been wondering
where you were!

238
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,500
I heard you
were trying to hoard

239
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:32,083
all the best food
in the joint for yourself.

240
00:11:32,166 --> 00:11:33,125
What's the deal there, girl?

241
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:34,875
The deal's takoyaki!

242
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:36,333
[USAMARU] And you betrayed us
after we all managed

243
00:11:36,416 --> 00:11:38,458
to get through the
first round, too, man.

244
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:40,041
