from the sound she manipulates

492
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:32,000
to increase the gravity
of specific areas.

493
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:34,208
And that's not all.

494
00:20:34,291 --> 00:20:35,458
[ERUNA]
She can fly?

495
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:38,375
So what, sound pressure
can manipulate gravity?

496
00:20:38,458 --> 00:20:41,000
No matter what Usamaru does,
he won't be able to reach her.

497
00:20:41,083 --> 00:20:42,875
How's that legal?
That's cheating!

498
00:20:42,958 --> 00:20:44,125
No, this is just what happens

499
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:46,375
when their abilities
don't match up, ryui.

500
00:20:46,458 --> 00:20:48,833
It may be horrible to watch,
but it is perfectly legal.

501
00:20:48,916 --> 00:20:51,958
Well why hasn't she gone ahead
and broken his last crystal yet?

502
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:53,791
It's not like he can do
anything to protect himself

503
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:55,125
in the state she's put him in.

504
00:20:55,208 --> 00:20:56,625
[TONKYUN]
She's toying with him.

505
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:59,750
Been doing it for a while now
and he can't resist.

506
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,791
She's just making a fool of him.

507
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,583
So not cool!

508
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:08,291
Oh, come on now, bunny boy,
why don't you give up already?

509
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:09,833
You've gotta know the truth.

510
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:11,666
You don't have a chance in hell
of winning this match,

511
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:13,375
so just surrender to me, kay?

512
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:14,916
Yeah, but don't you think
it would be cool as hell

513
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,375
if the underdog
could win this battle

514
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,875
after an unexpected comeback
move like in the movies?

515
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:19,875
[SAGARA]
Oh my god, no!

516
00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:21,166
What are you thinking?

517
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:23,250
That would be
the opposite of cool.

518
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:29,208
[ERUNA]
Usamaru! Just jump!

519
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:31,375
Jump as high as you can
and kick her snotty self

520
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:33,208
back to the ground!

521
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:34,666
Did you hear that, bunny?

522
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,416
It sounds like you've got
a little rodent friend

523
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:37,791
cheering you on out there.

524
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:39,791
I imagine you want to
hippity hop over to her

525
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:41,583
like a good little bunny-boy.

526
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:43,500
Hop all you want,
though, flopsy mopsy.

527
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:44,666
No matter what you do,

528
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:46,375
you'll never be able
to reach me up here!

529
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:49,625
[cacophony continues]

530
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:50,833
[USAMARU]
Eruna...

531
00:21:50,916 --> 00:21:52,333
I can't believe it...

532
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:55,458
You actually came to
cheer me on this time!

533
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:57,333
That's right!
And I'm not the only one!

534
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:59,166
Tonkyun came out
to cheer for you, too!

535
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,500
[USAMARU]
That makes me happy.

536
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:02,083
There's nothing more
passionately youthful

537
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:04,041
than an event where your
friends can cheer you on,

538
00:22:04,125 --> 00:22:05,916
which means one thing
for this bunny boy.

539
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,333
I've got this!

540
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,291
[ERUNA]
Usamaru!

541
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:21,041
Didn't I say from
the very beginning

542
00:22:21,125 --> 00:22:23,333
that bunnies were meant
to be hunted and taken down?

543
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:24,750
Why you didn't
just start crying then

544
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:28,208
and begging me to go easy
on you is beyond me.

545
00:22:28,291 --> 00:22:30,833
What do you think
you're doing by actually trying?

546
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:34,750
You're ruining the fun
for the rest of everybody.

547
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:37,458
This is why I hate
these damn club battles.

548
00:24:17,916 --> 00:24:19,625
[ERUNA]
Usamaru!

549
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:21,541
How could you lose
on me like that?

550
00:24:21,625 --> 00:24:24,875
Why didn't you use the special
ability "Passionate Sweat"?

551
00:24:24,958 --> 00:24:27,083
[BIMII] Because it's not
an actual ability, ryui.

552
00:24:27,166 --> 00:24:29,041
[ERUNA] What about the
sultriness ability, then?

553
00:24:29,125 --> 00:24:31,916
He condenses the steam created
by the hot air gushing from them

554
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,041
and then makes a
big, gaseous thing--

555
00:24:34,125 --> 00:24:36,000
[BIMII] Sounds like
con funk to me, ryui.

556
00:24:36,083 --> 00:24:38,291
[ERUNA] Okay, okay,
how about bare hands?

557
00:24:38,375 --> 00:24:39,958
After they duke it out
by a dry river,

558
00:24:40,041 --> 00:24:42,375
they make up by laughing
and rolling down the bank!

559
00:24:42,458 --> 00:24:44,458
[BIMII]
Also not an ability, Eruna.

560
00:24:44,541 --> 00:24:46,250
[ERUNA]
Why not? It's passionate youth,

561
00:24:46,333 --> 00:24:47,833
which can be found
in the shadows at night

562
00:24:47,916 --> 00:24:49,250
just before sunset.

563
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:51,458
[MINATOGAWA] The ability
"Youthful Bittersweet Memory."

564
00:24:51,541 --> 00:24:52,666
[ERUNA]
Minatogawa?

565
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:54,500
[BIMII] What kind of
ability is that, ryui?

566
00:24:54,583 --> 00:24:55,416
[MINATOGAWA]
Drool...

567
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,000
[ERUNA]
Huh?

568
00:24:57,083 --> 00:24:58,125
[MINATOGAWA] When you imagine
yourself eating something sour,

569
00:24:58,208 --> 00:24:59,583
so it makes your mouth water.

570
00:24:59,666 --> 00:25:03,041
[ERUNA] Uh... yeah,
I don't get it, like at all.

571
00:25:03,125 --> 00:25:05,458
Anyone else maybe know where
Minatogawa is coming from

572
00:25:05,541 --> 00:25:06,625
on this one?

573
00:25:06,708 --> 00:25:08,500
[MINATOGAWA]
Next time, "Junk Innocence."

574
00:25:08,583 --> 00:25:11,583
Perhaps Kuzuryu's past
will be revealed.

